  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "If you have a wait-listed ticket and the chart is prepared without your seat being confirmed, typically:\n\n1. If your ticket remains wait-listed (RAC or Waitlist status):\n- You will get a full refund\n- Refund can be claimed at the reservation counter\n- Refund process takes 5-7 working days\n\n2. If your ticket status is:\n- Confirmed: No refund\n- Not confirmed and remains in waiting list: Full refund applicable\n\n3. Refund process:\n- Online booking: Refund to original payment method\n- Offline booking: Refund at railway reservation counter\n- Refund will be processed after chart preparation\n\n4. Cancellation charges:\n- If cancelled before chart preparation: Minimal or no deduction\n- If cancelled after chart preparation: Standard cancellation charges apply\n\nAlways check the specific terms and conditions of your ticket and consult railway officials for the most accurate and updated information.",
